                <h4 class="text-light p-3">PLEASE FILL OUT ALL THE FIELDS BELOW</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-center mt-4">INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR AGREEMENT</p>
            <p>This Independent Contractor Agreement (this "Agreement") by and between ENZ Transport LLC, an Arizona limited liability company ("ENZ Transport") and <input type="text">
                , an ("Contractor") is effective as of this <input type="text">
                day of <input type="text">
                , 2023 (the “Effective Date”). The parties to this Agreement may individually be referred to as a “Party” and collectively as the “Parties.”</p>
            <p><b> RECITALS: </b><br>
           WHEREAS, ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC is a motor carrier with Operating authority as required by 49 U.S.C 375.205, 49 U.S.C 13902, 49 C.F.R part 365, 49 C.F.R Part 368 and 49 C.F.R part 392.9a, and ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC, desires to obtain services for the transportation of freight by truck utilizing independent contractors; and </p>
            <p><b>WHEREAS,</b> Contractor is separately engaged in the business of transporting freight by truck on behalf of public and private entities under operating agreements; and is a motor carrier with operating authority as required by 49 U.S.C 375.205, 49 U.S.C. 13902, 49 C.F.R part 368 and 49. C.F.R. part 392.9a; and </p>
            <p><b>WHEREAS,</b> ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC and Contractor intend to create and maintain under the terms of this Agreement an independent contractor relationship and not a relationship of employer and employee; and</p>
            <p><b>WHEREAS,</b> ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC desires to utilize the services and equipment of Contractor, and Contractor desires to render motor freight transportation service to ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC in the course of Contractor's established trade, business and profession; and</p>
            <p><b>WHEREAS,</b> Contractor represents that he/she/it is the owner, or is in valid possession of tractor/power units and has legal capacity to enter into this Agreement and commit such tractor/power unit(s) and /or personnel services for utilization under this Agreement, and <br>
            WHEREAS, ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC and Contractor desire to enter into this Agreement for the purpose of carrying out the above mentioned obligations in accordance with the provisions set forth below.</p>    
            <p>In consideration of the mutual promises contained herein and for good and valuable consideration the parties agree as follows: </p>
            <p><b>1. Relationship</b> of the Parties. ENZ hereby retains the services of Contractor and Contractor hereby agrees to provide services to ENZ upon the terms and conditions set forth herein. Contractor is an independent contractor of ENZ, and this Agreement shall not be construed to create any association, partnership, joint venture, employee, or agency relationship between Contractor and ENZ for any purpose. Contractor will not be eligible to participate in any vacation, group medical or life insurance, disability, or retirement benefits, or any other fringe benefits or benefit plans, other than specified herein, and ENZ will not be responsible for withholding or paying any income, payroll, Social Security, or other federal, state, or local taxes, making any insurance contributions, including for unemployment or disability, or obtaining workers' compensation insurance on Contractor’s behalf, unless otherwise provide herein. Contractor shall be responsible for and shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless ENZ against all such taxes or contributions, including but not limited to penalties and interest. Any persons employed or engaged by Contractor in connection with the performance of the Services shall be Contractor’s employees or contractors and Contractor shall be fully responsible for them and indemnify, defend, and hold harmless ENZ against any and all claims made by or on behalf of any such employee or contractor. </p>    
            <p><b>2. Independent Contractor:</b> Contractor is an Independent Contractor and any and all persons hired by or employed by Contractor to perform services in connection with this Agreement are the employees or agents of Contractor, and not those of ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC. Contractor has and shall retain sole financial and legal responsibility for compliance with all applicable worker's compensation insurance requirements, withholding and employment taxes due to federal, state, or local governments on account of drivers, driver's helpers, and other workers necessary for the performance of Contractor's obligations hereunder. Contractor agrees to indemnify, save and hold harmless ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC from any and all claims by Contractor, Contractor's employees, Contractor's drivers, driver's helpers, agents, and any other workers used by it or by any federal, state or local governmental agency on account of wages, industrial accident, unemployment compensation claims, or workers' compensation claims, tax, withholding and Employment taxes: or any other actions rising from employment taxes; or any other actions arising from contractor’s relationship with its own employees. It is further agreed that any property damage, bodily injury, and/or any other harm or damage sustained by contractor's drivers or caused by Contractor's drivers to unauthorized passengers, will be the sole responsibility of Contractor. To help fulfill Contractor's obligations under this paragraph, Contractor agrees to: <br>

                • Maintain in effect, at all times, workers' compensation insurance as required by applicable state statutes and regulations, for all employee drivers, driver's helpers, agents, and laborers used to Contractor in the performance of this Agreement; <br>
                
                • File and pay all applicable state and local income taxes, tax withholding, employment, unemployment, taxes and returns, federal heavy vehicle use tax forms and returns, all of which it may be required to file on account of its employed drivers, driver's helpers and agents, and laborers used by Contractor in the performance of this agreement at the time and place specified in applicable federal, state and local laws and regulations and to report and pay when due all such taxes and contributions required to be paid in such forms and returns <br>
                
                • With respect to the requirement of subparagraphs (a) and (b) above, Contractor will furnish to ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC such evidence of compliance with the foregoing as ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC shall reasonably request. </p>    
            <p><b>3. Term.</b> The term of this Agreement shall begin on the Effective Date and shall continue until (a) this Agreement has been terminated as provided herein or (b) either Party gives the other Party written notice of their desire to terminate.</p>
            <p><b> 4. Duties.</b>    Contractor is engaged to provide various driving and trucking services for ENZ (the “Services”). Contractor agrees to perform his/her duties in full compliance with ENZ’s guidelines, policies, and procedures. Contractor shall perform such duties as are required to maintain the quality and reputation of ENZ. Contractor agrees to comply with all applicable laws and regulations and applicable professional standards. Contractor certifies and affirms that she/he is in possession of an active and valid CDL license, or the applicable license to perform all Services. Contractor shall provide ENZ with written notice of any license suspension within twenty-four (24) hours of such suspension or prior to performing any Services, whichever occurs first.</p>
            <p><b> 5. Compensation.</b> As full compensation for the Services and rights granted to Contractor in this Agreement, ENZ shall pay Contractor Cents ($0.60) per mile/ split (the "Compensation"). During training, contractor will be receiving only $500 regardless of miles driven. Contractor acknowledges that she/he will receive an IRS Form 1099-MISC from ENZ, and Contractor shall be solely responsible for all federal, state, and local taxes. ENZ agrees to reimburse Contractor for expenses that have been pre-approved in writing.</p>
            <p> <b>6. Payment Terms.</b> ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC shall pay contractor the compensation not later than 14 days after submission by Contractor to ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC of the following shipping documents, unless a good faith dispute exists, in which case ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC shall be entitled to contest the compensation: (a) driver's logs as required by governmental authorities evidencing delivery of freight from point of pickup to point of destination; (b) original bills of lading and/or delivery receipts; (c) such other documents as ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC is required to submit to secure payment from a shipper; and (d) completed trip cost report evidencing point of pickup to point of destination.</p>
            <p><b> 7. Authorized Deductions:</b> Contractor authorizes ENZ Transport, LLC to deduct expenses, for the following items from any Payment due or to come due to Contractor under the terms of this Agreement: <br>

                • Advances made by ENZ Transport, LLC to Contractor, and an administrative charge of $10.00 for making such advance. <br>
               
                • Any federal or state taxes, fines, citations, levies made against ENZ Transport, LLC on behalf of Contractor. <br>
               
                • Any damage to ENZ Transport, LLC equipment not to exceed $2500. </p>
            <p><b>8. Non-solicitation.</b> During the Term of this Agreement and for a period of one (1) year after termination or expiration, Contractor shall not, directly or indirectly: (1) solicit, induce, or attempt to solicit or induce any referral source, contractor, reseller, consultant, employee, customer, licensee, vendor, or other business relation of ENZ to cease doing business with ENZ, or in an way interfere with the relationship between any employee, contractor, reseller, consultant, customer, or business relation of ENZ; or (2) sell to or solicit sales from any customer or account which was a customer or account of ENZ as of the termination or expiration of this Agreement or within one (1) year prior, or with which Contractor had contact or about which Contractor had Confidential Information by reason of Contractor’s work with ENZ.</p>
            <p><b>9. Performance Standards.</b> In performing Services under this Agreement, Contractor shall (i) use diligent efforts and professional skills and judgment; (ii) perform Services in accordance with recognized standards of professionalism; (iii) comply with the directives, policies, rules, and regulations of ENZ, (iv) provide Services in an efficient and cost-effective manner; and (v) comply with all applicable federal, state, and local laws and regulations. It is agreed that ENZ shall exercise no control over the actions of Contractor in his/her engagement with ENZ.</p>
            <p> <b>10. Compliance With Applicable Laws:</b> Contractor shall comply, at all times, with all applicable laws and regulations governing performance of this Agreement including, but not limited to, loading and securement of freight, driver safety regulations including but not limited to hiring, use of controlled substances, and hours of service, sanitation and temperature requirements for transporting food and other perishables, maintenance of equipment, and control of the means and method of transportation including but not limited to performance of Contractor's drivers. ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC shall comply with applicable federal and state laws and regulation relating to its performance hereunder. Compliance with applicable laws and regulations by each of the Parties shall be subject to verification by either of them at any time of reasonable request. CONTRACTOR SHALL COMPLY WITH ALL LAWS, RULES AND REGULATIONS REGARDING PASSENGERS WHILE PROVIDING FREIGHT TRANSPORTATION SERVICES FOR THE BENEFIT OF ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC (under 49 CFR 392.60). Without limiting the foregoing, Contractor agrees to maintain in Contractor's possession in the Equipment during its operation at all times during the performance of this Agreements, a copy of this Agreement.</p>
            <p><b>11. Liability/Failed Delivery:</b> In the event that Contractor fails to complete a trip, abandons a shipment, or otherwise subjects ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC to liability, directly or indirectly related to Contractor's failure to perform or to perform adequately, ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC shall have the right to complete performance in any reasonable manner or method, using the Equipment or any substituted equipment. ENZ TRANSPORT, LLC may charge Contractor for such costs, expenses, losses or damages including but not limited to reasonable attorney fees, incurred to complete performance, either directly or deducted them from Settlement due or to come due to Contractor. </p>
            <p><b>12. Contractor Confidentiality.</b> Contractor acknowledges that as a result of its Agreement hereunder, Contractor will be making use of, acquiring, and adding to information of a confidential, special and unique nature and value. Contractor agrees that he/she shall not, at any time during the course of the Agreement with ENZ, and at any time thereafter upon termination of the Agreement, for any reason whatsoever, directly or indirectly, communicate, divulge, or disclose to or use for the benefit of any person, corporation, or entity, or herself/himself, for any purpose whatsoever, any information concerning any matters affecting or relating to ENZ, including but not limited to confidential client information of ENZ. Contractor acknowledges and expressly agrees that all of such information is important, material, confidential, and secret and significantly affects the successful conduct of ENZ and its goodwill, and that any breach of the terms of this paragraph shall be a material breach of this Agreement and cause for immediate termination of the Agreement and for such other legal remedies as ENZ may elect to pursue. In the event of a breach or threatened breach by Contractor of any of the provisions of this paragraph, ENZ ,in addition to and not in limitation of any of the rights, remedies, or damages available to ENZ under this Agreement, at law or in equity, shall be entitled to a permanent injunction in order to prevent or restrain any such breach by Contractor or by Contractor 's future partners, agents, representatives, servants, resellers, or by any and all persons directly or indirectly acting for or with her/him. Confidential Information shall not include information that: (a) is or becomes generally available to the public other than through Contractor’s breach of this Agreement; or (b) is communicated to Contractor by a third party that had no confidentiality obligations with respect to such information. Nothing herein shall be construed to prevent disclosure of Confidential Information as may be required by applicable law or regulation, or pursuant to the valid order of a court of competent jurisdiction or an authorized government agency, provided that the disclosure does not exceed the extent of disclosure required by such law, regulation, or order. Contractor agrees to provide written notice of any such order to an authorized officer of ENZ within five (5) business days of receiving such order, but in any event sufficiently in advance of making any disclosure to permit ENZ to contest the order or seek confidentiality protections, as determined in ENZ's sole discretion. </p>
            <p><b>13. Ownership of Property.</b> Contractor further acknowledges and expressly agrees that all files, records, lists, books, literature, documents, photos, equipment, emails, social media posts, correspondence, products, services, code, source code, graphics, client lists, products, financials, prospects, and any data of any type whatsoever related to the business of ENZ or its clients, vendors, and partners or used by it, in connection with its business, shall at all times remain the property of ENZ, and that upon termination of the Agreement hereunder for any reason whatsoever, Contractor shall surrender and deliver to ENZ all such information and materials. </p>
            <p><b>14. Termination.</b> (a) ENZ and Contractor agree that Contractor may terminate this Agreement without cause by giving ENZ at least seven (7) days advance written notice. If Contractor fails to provide seven (7) days written notice of termination, then Contractor shall be obligated for $500 administrative fee to be deducted from the Contractor’s last scheduled payment. On the effective date of termination, ENZ shall pay to Contractor any undisputed amount of compensation due to Contractor through the effective date of termination as stated by the laws of Arizona.  <br>

                (b) Notwithstanding any other provision hereof, ENZ may terminate this Agreement at any time without notice for "cause." For purposes hereof, the term "cause" shall include, without limitation: <br>
                
                (i) Contractor commits an act or omits to take an act that in the good faith and reasonable belief of ENZ jeopardized, or could have jeopardized, ENZ’s reputation and/or goodwill in the market; <br>
                
              16. Non-disparagement. Contractor agrees to not at any time make any public statements, whether orally or in writing, that are intended to be derogatory or damaging to ENZ or any of ENZ’s officers, employees, directors, partners, agents or shareholders or take any action that would reasonably be expected to adversely affect ENZ’s personal or professional reputation.    (ii) 
                
                Contractor has criminal charges filed against her/him, which, in the good faith determination of ENZ are detrimental to the reputation of ENZ, which includes but is not limited to fraud, theft, or a conviction of a felony;  <br>
                
                (iii) Conduct, which is in violation of any provision of this Agreement or any ENZ policies, procedures, or rules; or   <br>
                
                (iv) Conduct, which is in violation of any provision of Schedule 1 of this Agreement. (c) This Agreement shall terminate on the date of Contractor's death if not sooner terminated.  <br>
                
                (d) This Agreement shall terminate upon the liquidation, dissolution, or bankruptcy of ENZ or the sale of all or substantially all of the assets or outstanding capital stock of ENZ. <br>
                
                (e) This Agreement shall terminate upon mutual written agreement of ENZ and Contractor. <br>
                
                (F) Contractor has 7-day period to retrieve all personal belongings from the truck. </p>
            <p><b>15. Limitation of Liability.</b> ENZ's liability to Contractor under this Agreement, in the event of a wrongful termination or any other breach of any provision of this Agreement, shall not exceed an amount of money equaling one month of Compensation paid to Contractor. </p>
            <p><b>16. Non-disparagement.</b> Contractor agrees to not at any time make any public statements, whether orally or in writing, that are intended to be derogatory or damaging to ENZ or any of ENZ’s officers, employees, directors, partners, agents or shareholders or take any action that would reasonably be expected to adversely affect ENZ’s personal or professional reputation. </p>
            <p><b>17. Benefits.</b> Contractor shall be entitled to no benefits. </p>
            <p><b>18. Survival of Covenants and Agreements.</b> Contractor acknowledges and agrees that Contractor's obligations, covenants, and agreements under Paragraphs 5,7,8,10,11,19,21 shall survive the termination of this Agreement. </p>
            <p><b>19. Modification of Agreement.</b> No waiver or modification of this Agreement shall be valid unless it is in writing and duly executed by both parties.</p>
            <p><b>20. Severability.</b> If any term or provision of this Agreement is invalid, illegal, or unenforceable in any jurisdiction, such invalidity, illegality, or unenforceability shall not affect any other term or provision of this Agreement or invalidate or render unenforceable such term or provision in any other jurisdiction. </p>
            <p><b>21. Choice of Law.</b> It is the intention of the parties that this Agreement and its performance and all suits and special proceedings hereunder be construed in accordance with and under and pursuant to the laws of the state of Arizona and that in any action, special proceeding or other proceedings that may be brought, arising out of, in connection with, or by reason of this Agreement, the laws of the state of Arizona shall be applicable and shall govern to the exclusion of the law of any other forum, without regard to the jurisdiction in which any action or special proceeding may be instituted</p>
            <p><b>22. Waiver.</b> The waiver by either party of any breach or violation of any provision of this Agreement shall not operate or be construed as a waiver of any subsequent breach or violation hereof. </p>
            <p><b>23. Contractor Representations and Warranties.</b> Contractor represents and warrants to ENZ that: (a) Contractor has the right to enter into this Agreement, to grant the rights granted herein and to perform fully all of Contractor’s obligations in this Agreement; (b) entering into this Agreement with ENZ and Contractor’s performance of the Services do not and will not conflict with or result in any breach or default under any other agreement to which Contractor is subject; (c) Contractor has the required skill, experience, license, and qualifications to perform the Services and Contractor shall perform the Services in a professional and workmanlike manner in accordance with best industry standards for similar services and Contractor shall devote sufficient resources to ensure that the Services are performed in a timely and reliable manner; (d) Contractor shall perform the Services in compliance with all applicable federal, state, and local laws and regulations; and (e) Contractor shall not reverse engineer or export, directly or indirectly, any technical data acquired from ENZ, or any products utilizing any such data, to any country in violation of any applicable export laws or regulations. </p>
            <p><b>24. Indemnification.</b> (a) Contractor shall defend, indemnify, and hold harmless ENZ and its affiliates and their officers, directors, employees, agents, successors, and assigns from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, deficiencies, actions, judgments, interest, awards, penalties, fines, costs, or expenses of whatever kind (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or resulting from this Agreement. Contractor shall indemnify and defend ENZ and hold it harmless from and against any finding by any governmental entity.  <br>

                (b) Contractor acknowledges and understands that ENZ shall not be providing any insurance coverage, including but not limited to worker’s compensation insurance. If Contractor chooses to carry or transport any passengers, while performing the Services, Contractor shall indemnify, defend, and hold ENZ harmless from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, deficiencies, actions, judgments, interest, awards, penalties, fines, costs, or expenses of whatever kind (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or resulting from injury or death of any passengers, including but not limited to animals.   <br>
                (c) Contractor shall reimburse ENZ Transport for any damage to a ENZ Transport vehicle, while performing the Services, in an amount equal to or less than Two Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($2,500.00) (the “Contractor Truck Liability”). Contractor acknowledges and agrees that ENZ Transport will not file any claims for any damages that are considered Contractor Truck Liability.</p>
            <p><b>Benefit.</b> This Agreement shall inure to, and shall be binding upon, the successors and assigns of the Parties. <br>

                <b>26. Arbitration.</b> Any and all disputes over the interpretation, enforcement, or application of any of the terms of this Agreement shall initially be resolved by both Parties engaging in good faith negotiations no less than ten (10) days following the dispute. In the event good faith negotiations do not resolve said dispute, then any dispute, claim or controversy between or among the parties to this Agreement arising out of or relating to this Agreement or any breach thereof, including, without limitation, any claim that this Agreement or any of its parts is invalid, illegal or otherwise voidable or void, whether such dispute, claim or controversy sounds in contract, tort, equity or otherwise, and whether such dispute, claim or controversy relates to the meaning, interpretation, effect, validity, performance or enforcement of the Agreement, such dispute, claim or controversy shall be settled by and through an arbitration proceeding to be administered by the American Arbitration Association (or any like organization successor thereto) in Phoenix, Arizona, in accordance with the American Arbitration Association’s Commercial Arbitration Rules. Each of the parties to this Agreement hereby agrees and consents to such venue and waives any objection thereto. The arbitrability of any such dispute, claim or controversy shall likewise be determined in such arbitration. Such arbitration proceeding shall be conducted in as expedited a manner as is then permitted by the commercial arbitration rules (formal or informal) of the American Arbitration Association. Both the foregoing agreement of the parties to this Agreement to arbitrate any and all such disputes, claims and controversies and the results, determinations, findings, judgments and/or awards rendered through any such arbitration shall be final and binding on the parties hereto and may be specifically enforced by legal proceedings. In connection with any dispute arising out of or concerning this Agreement, the prevailing party shall be entitled to recover its’ reasonable attorneys’ fees and costs.</p>
            <p> <b>27. Notices.</b> Any notice required under this Agreement shall be sufficient, if given in writing, and if sent by electronic mail to ENZ at: Admin@bluelinetransport.me; and to Contractor's email at <input type="text">
                . *</p>
            <p><b>28. Entire Agreement.</b> This Agreement contains the complete agreement between the Parties. The Parties acknowledge that any statements or representations that may have been made previously by either of them to the other are of no effect and that neither of them has relied on such considerations in concluding this Agreement. Each Party acknowledges that he or it has had full and fair opportunity to seek independent counsel with respect to this Agreement. </p>    
            <p><b>29. Paragraph Headings. </b>The headings in this Agreement are inserted for convenience and identification only and are in no way intended to describe, interpret, define or limit the scope or intent of this Agreement or any provision hereof. </p>    
            <p><b>30. Counterparts.</b> This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts with the same effect as if all parties had signed the same document. All counterparts shall be construed together and shall constitute one (1) agreement.</p>    
            <p><b>31. Assignment Prohibited.</b>  This Agreement is personal to the Contractor and Contractor shall not or may not delegate or assign any of his rights or obligations under this Agreement. </p>
            <p><b>32. Declaration of Independent Contractor Status.</b> Contractor shall execute the Declaration of Independent Status in Schedule 2, incorporated herein. Contractor further agrees to execute an IRS Form W-9 within five (5) days of the execution of this Agreement. Page 8 of 12</p>
            <p><b>33. Waiver of Workers Compensation.</b> Contractor shall execute the Sole Proprietor/Independent Contractor form in Schedule 3, referenced and incorporated herein. </p>
            <p><b>34. Transportation Occupational Accident Election. </b>Contractor shall execute the Transportation Occupational Accident Individual Request form in Schedule 4, referenced and incorporated herein. Contractor shall accept or decline coverage whereby if accepted, Contractor shall have $155 deducted from their monthly pay.</p>
            <p>  IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Agreement to be executed as of the date first written above. </p> 
            <p>ENZ Transport LL</p>
            <p>By:  HFAISAL</p>
